# Unqualified "%=" doesn't seem to work properly once conditionals are
# used.  It appears that screen counts bytes instead of characters.
# The examples below compensate for this using offsets calculated
# using trial and error.

# This example includes the time, which causes screen to redraw the
# caption every minute.  It seems to redraw in a way where the end
# attribute is erased, causing the subsequent region to briefly be
# reverse video, making the screen flash.
caption string "%?%F󵈣%:󵈡%?%3n %t%-012=%c󵈠"

# Use this version without the time if the flashing is annoying.
#caption string "%?%F󵈣%:󵈡%?%3n %t%-07=󵈠"
